00:00:00.550 --> 00:00:02.110
Problem 38.

00:00:02.110 --> 00:00:05.080
In the drawing below, the figure
formed by the squares

00:00:05.080 --> 00:00:09.650
with sides that are labeled x,
y, and z is a right triangle.

00:00:09.650 --> 00:00:11.680
So the figure, so it's
a right triangle.

00:00:14.550 --> 00:00:16.990
And then they ask us, which
equation is true for all

00:00:16.990 --> 00:00:19.350
values of x, y, and z?

00:00:19.350 --> 00:00:21.870
So really, they're just trying
to see if you remember the

00:00:21.870 --> 00:00:23.190
Pythagorean Theorem.

00:00:31.050 --> 00:00:34.980
And that just tells us that if
we have a right triangle, that

00:00:34.980 --> 00:00:40.050
the sum of the squares of the
two smaller sides, so x

00:00:40.050 --> 00:00:44.440
squared plus y squared, is
going to be equal to the

00:00:44.440 --> 00:00:48.240
square of the longest side, or
the side that's opposite the

00:00:48.240 --> 00:00:49.010
right angle.

00:00:49.010 --> 00:00:50.260
Or we also call that
the hypotenuse.

00:00:53.540 --> 00:00:55.890
So that's equal to z squared.

00:00:55.890 --> 00:00:58.420
That's what the Pythagorean
Theorem tells us.

00:00:58.420 --> 00:01:02.120
And so if we look down here,
only one of those match what I

00:01:02.120 --> 00:01:04.670
just wrote down, are kind
of my restatement of the

00:01:04.670 --> 00:01:06.090
Pythagorean Theorem.

00:01:06.090 --> 00:01:09.570
x squared plus y squared
is equal to z squared.

00:01:09.570 --> 00:01:13.350
And that's this one right
there, choice B.

