00:02:00.270 --> 00:02:04.220
So when I take its reflection,
I would draw it right here, 1

00:02:04.220 --> 00:02:07.520
to the right of the y-axis.

00:02:07.520 --> 00:02:13.580
This line down here, it goes
from 1 to the left all the way

00:02:13.580 --> 00:02:15.140
to 4 to the left.

00:02:15.140 --> 00:02:17.370
On this side, it's going to go
from 1 to the right all the

00:02:17.370 --> 00:02:20.610
way to 4 to the right.

00:02:20.610 --> 00:02:22.470
I could keep doing it.

00:02:22.470 --> 00:02:26.180
This segment right here, FE,
when I flip it, will become

00:02:26.180 --> 00:02:28.850
this segment right here.

00:02:28.850 --> 00:02:34.800
This segment, DE, right here,
will become this segment.

00:02:34.800 --> 00:02:38.190
It'll just look something like
this when I go onto that side.

00:02:38.190 --> 00:02:43.210
And then C, right here, is 2
to the left of the y-axis.

00:02:43.210 --> 00:02:46.710
So C over here will be 2 to
the right of the y-axis.

00:02:46.710 --> 00:02:48.630
So it's going to look
something like this.

00:02:48.630 --> 00:02:52.130
So the vest is going to look
something like this.

00:02:52.130 --> 00:02:54.030
And then of course, it just
dips down like that.

00:02:54.030 --> 00:02:56.230
So that's the right-hand
side of the vest.

00:02:56.230 --> 00:02:58.240
But they want to know what
are the coordinates of C?

00:02:58.240 --> 00:03:01.330
So this is C, and this is the
