00:03:30.690 --> 00:03:31.880
Number 40.

00:03:31.880 --> 00:03:34.920
What is the area, in
square units, of

00:03:34.920 --> 00:03:38.540
trapezoid QRST shown below?

00:03:38.540 --> 00:03:40.276
So we need to figure out
the area of this.

00:03:40.276 --> 00:03:42.190
And they actually even
give us a formula.

00:03:42.190 --> 00:03:46.090
They gave us the formula
for this trapezoid.

00:03:46.090 --> 00:03:52.810
So they're calling it 1/2 times
the height, times base 1

00:03:52.810 --> 00:03:54.150
plus base 2.

00:03:54.150 --> 00:03:55.980
So essentially, just to give you
an intuition of where this

00:03:55.980 --> 00:03:58.410
comes from, you're essentially
saying, what's the average

00:03:58.410 --> 00:04:00.360
width of this trapezoid?

00:04:00.360 --> 00:04:05.195
So you take 1/2 times the sum of
this guy and that guy, and

00:04:05.195 --> 00:04:06.830
that gives you the
average width.

00:04:06.830 --> 00:04:08.640
And then you multiply that
times the height.

00:04:08.640 --> 00:04:15.450
So just applying this formula,
it is 1/2 times my height-- my

00:04:15.450 --> 00:04:21.500
height is 8-- times base 1,
let's call this base 1, 20.

00:04:21.500 --> 00:04:23.320
Plus base 2.

00:04:23.320 --> 00:04:25.980
Base 2 is this 6 right there.

00:04:25.980 --> 00:04:30.200
So I have 1/2 times 8,
which is 4, times 26.

00:04:30.200 --> 00:04:36.000
And 4 times 26 is equal
to 104 square units.

00:04:36.000 --> 00:04:37.310
So that's that right there.

00:04:37.310 --> 00:04:38.570
So they're really just
testing whether you

00:04:38.570 --> 00:04:39.750
can apply this formula.

00:04:39.750 --> 00:04:42.020
Whether you can recognize what's
the height and what are

00:04:42.020 --> 00:04:44.750
the two bases.

